00:25:10,940 --> 00:25:15,234
You forgot about the money.
I have all the goddamn money.

252
00:25:16,279 --> 00:25:18,401
You keep that little $15,000, Ray.

253
00:25:20,742 --> 00:25:22,116
He's right, baby.

254
00:25:22,451 --> 00:25:25,951
We should sell the stuff in Houston.
Think of all the money.

255
00:25:27,665 --> 00:25:31,958
We'll be okay.
Pluto knows people in Chicago.

256
00:25:32,503 --> 00:25:35,076
We can live off that money for a long time.

257
00:25:36,383 --> 00:25:38,671
Come on, baby, it's going to be okay.

258
00:25:41,011 --> 00:25:43,881
We can buy all the blow we want
when we get there.

259
00:25:45,223 --> 00:25:46,635
We'll be safe.

260
00:25:47,601 --> 00:25:49,393
Pluto will take care of us.

261
00:25:50,688 --> 00:25:52,181
We'll be safe, baby.

262
00:26:31,227 --> 00:26:32,934
This is really beautiful.

263
00:26:33,395 --> 00:26:35,019
It's as green as hell.

264
00:26:36,190 --> 00:26:37,981
You know I'm a country boy.

265
00:26:38,109 --> 00:26:40,315
That's crap. You were born in L.A.

266
00:26:41,528 --> 00:26:42,524
Malibu.

267
00:26:50,913 --> 00:26:52,703
What the fuck?

268
00:27:01,840 --> 00:27:02,836
Howdy.

269
00:27:04,675 --> 00:27:10,096
Welcome to Star City. We've got
a full day, so follow me to the motel...

270
00:27:10,514 --> 00:27:13,385
...you can unpack
and we'll get something to eat.

271
00:27:13,685 --> 00:27:17,551
When I saw you drive by,
I knew you were the boys from California.

272
00:27:18,230 --> 00:27:20,601
Cops look the same everywhere, I guess.

273
00:27:22,233 --> 00:27:23,314
Follow me.

274
00:27:28,699 --> 00:27:29,813
Oh, shit.

275
00:27:48,218 --> 00:27:50,091
You boys are in for a treat.

276
00:27:51,721 --> 00:27:53,927
Fern, can we get some more biscuits?

277
00:27:54,223 --> 00:27:57,010
-Sure, Hurricane.
-And more coffee.

278
00:27:57,602 --> 00:27:58,681
Hurricane?

279
00:27:58,853 --> 00:28:01,688
Some folks call me that.
I never figured out why.

280
00:28:04,274 --> 00:28:08,403
We can wait in the woods.
When the bad folks show up...

281
00:28:09,195 --> 00:28:11,605
...we'll put the stopper in the bottle.

282
00:28:11,741 --> 00:28:14,195
They'll be sorry they ever heard
of Star City.

283
00:28:14,327 --> 00:28:15,489
This is good.

284
00:28:17,120 --> 00:28:19,077
My mother used to make food like this.

285
00:28:19,205 --> 00:28:20,913
Thanks. How's Walter?

286
00:28:21,208 --> 00:28:23,165
He had gallbladder surgery.

287
00:28:23,378 --> 00:28:26,745
Good for him. I'll be giving you boys
my full cooperation.

288
00:28:27,548 --> 00:28:29,255
Me and my two deputies...

289
00:28:29,590 --> 00:28:33,291
...will take turns watching the place
around the clock.

290
00:28:34,052 --> 00:28:38,845
So you boys can just relax, drink beer,
chase chicks, and whatever.

291
00:28:39,142 --> 00:28:40,635
We'll help.

292
00:28:40,934 --> 00:28:42,927
-We'll help you.
-Suit yourself.

293
00:28:44,397 --> 00:28:46,519
Another thing. Old Man Malcolm...

294
00:28:47,234 --> 00:28:50,851
...l guarantee he don't know jack-shit
about what his nephew did.

295
00:28:53,031 --> 00:28:54,441
Did you talk to him?

296
00:28:55,490 --> 00:28:59,904
Not yet. I just know. There aren't even
any telephone lines up there.

297
00:29:00,496 --> 00:29:03,201
He's a hermit.
Hardly ever leaves his property.

298
00:29:03,999 --> 00:29:06,490
I think we ought to talk to him
and let him know.

299
00:29:06,919 --> 00:29:09,954
-That may be the case, but--
-Charlie! Get on in here.

300
00:29:10,338 --> 00:29:12,877
This is my deputy. Retired police officer.

301
00:29:13,424 --> 00:29:15,168
Charlie, this is Dud Cole.

302
00:29:16,594 --> 00:29:19,050
And this is Dan Macintosh.

303
00:29:19,264 --> 00:29:21,055
John. John McFeely.

304
00:29:21,515 --> 00:29:25,384
Oh, right. All them Mac names
sound alike to me.

305
00:29:26,021 --> 00:29:28,772
-You eaten, Charlie?
-Yeah, Jocelyn fixed me--

306
00:29:28,940 --> 00:29:30,979
Charlie's a Yankee from Detroit.

307
00:29:31,692 --> 00:29:35,310
Dale, if we talk to this guy
and he's involved--

308
00:29:35,488 --> 00:29:38,822
-I told you he's not.
-Hurricane. I mean, Dale.

309
00:29:39,408 --> 00:29:41,199
These are dangerous people.

310
00:29:41,493 --> 00:29:42,904
I understand that.

311
00:29:46,708 --> 00:29:47,906
You boys about ready?

312
00:29:48,042 --> 00:29:49,240
Just a second.

313
00:29:49,627 --> 00:29:50,741
Here, Fern.

314
00:29:51,211 --> 00:29:52,539
Keep the change.

315
00:29:52,838 --> 00:29:55,673
There is no change, Hurricane.
It's a $12 check...

316
00:29:55,799 --> 00:29:57,708
...and you gave me a ten!

317
00:29:57,843 --> 00:29:59,171
Catch you later.

318
00:29:59,553 --> 00:30:01,047
Is he gone?

319
00:30:01,263 --> 00:30:04,512
I haven't had a full meal
since I met the son of a bitch.

320
00:30:05,642 --> 00:30:07,100
Go ahead, Jimmy.

321
00:30:07,227 --> 00:30:10,513
It's Harlan Childress. Lureen called.
He's raising hell.

322
00:30:11,106 --> 00:30:15,055
I'm on a case here. Unless he's trying
to kill her, I don't have time.

323
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:17,525
She said he's trying to kill her.

324
00:30:18,571 --> 00:30:20,278
I'mjustletting you know.

325
00:30:20,573 --> 00:30:21,817
Okay, 10-4.

326
00:30:22,158 --> 00:30:25,941
Hop in. We have to make a little stop
before we go to the Malcolm place.

327
00:30:39,966 --> 00:30:41,211
Open this door!

328
00:30:41,385 --> 00:30:42,926
Goddamn it! Lureen!

329
00:30:45,346 --> 00:30:47,138
Harlan! Goddamn it.

330
00:30:51,311 --> 00:30:54,929
-Settle down, Harlan!
-Let go!

331
00:30:57,192 --> 00:30:58,651
Harlan, goddamn it!

332
00:31:03,364 --> 00:31:06,116
You calm down now. Calm down.

333
00:31:06,534 --> 00:31:08,692
Do you want to take a ride with me?

334
00:31:11,539 --> 00:31:14,161
-Settle down.
-He was out all night drinking.

335
00:31:15,959 --> 00:31:17,619
Who are those men?

336
00:31:18,045 --> 00:31:19,243
It's okay.

337
00:31:19,963 --> 00:31:21,956
She locked me out of the kitchen.

338
00:31:22,091 --> 00:31:23,550
I understand.

339
00:31:28,263 --> 00:31:29,971
You were out all night drinking.

340
00:31:30,099 --> 00:31:32,767
You knew she was going to do this,
didn't you?

341
00:31:35,103 --> 00:31:37,392
If you apologise, she may let you in.

342
00:31:37,522 --> 00:31:38,933
He knows I will.

343
00:31:39,774 --> 00:31:42,016
We'll go to church, he'll feel better.

344
00:31:42,152 --> 00:31:43,562
All right, Lureen.

345
00:31:45,447 --> 00:31:49,361
-You won't let them take him away?
-They're with me. They're from L.A.

346
00:31:50,409 --> 00:31:53,161
Get up. Pull yourself together, okay?
Come on.

347
00:31:54,204 --> 00:31:56,244
Come on. Get up.

348
00:31:59,126 --> 00:32:00,751
Now come here.

349
00:32:01,087 --> 00:32:04,455
Do me a favour.
Put this axe back in the shed.

350
00:32:04,673 --> 00:32:05,704
All right?

351
00:32:07,051 --> 00:32:10,716
I don't want to have to come back
out here. Are you okay?

352
00:32:10,888 --> 00:32:12,216
I'm okay.

353
00:32:13,974 --> 00:32:17,473
Put that axe in the shed.
And fix this window.

354
00:32:17,894 --> 00:32:20,978
-Tell Cheryl Ann and the baby I said hi.
-Tell them hi.

355
00:32:22,566 --> 00:32:24,854
-Sorry about the window.
-That's okay.

356
00:32:28,488 --> 00:32:32,022
It's okay, boys. I'm out here twice a week.

357
00:33:03,814 --> 00:33:04,975
Motherfucker!

358
00:33:07,442 --> 00:33:11,310
Goddamn it! They know me now.
Are you aware of that, bitch?

359
00:33:11,572 --> 00:33:15,486
They know my face, my name,
probably how long my dick is!

360
00:33:16,534 --> 00:33:20,532
A goddamn kid! Why didn't you tell me
about that fucking kid?

361
00:33:20,663 --> 00:33:23,237
I swear to God, I didn't see any kid!

362
00:33:24,209 --> 00:33:25,951
He must have been hiding.

363
00:33:26,336 --> 00:33:27,415
Quit lying!

364
00:33:27,962 --> 00:33:32,089
Don't hit me no more.
Pluto, don't let him hit me no more.

365
00:33:33,050 --> 00:33:34,628
Get rid of her, Ray.

366
00:33:35,636 --> 00:33:37,011
We'll be okay.

367
00:33:37,138 --> 00:33:40,471
-Shut up.
-We'll dump the car. They won't find us.

368
00:33:40,598 --> 00:33:42,342
They won't find you maybe!

369
00:33:42,476 --> 00:33:44,219
They won't find us!

370
00:33:44,519 --> 00:33:47,307
-It'll be okay.
-Get your hand off of me.

371
00:33:47,648 --> 00:33:49,225
We'll be okay.

372
00:33:59,617 --> 00:34:01,527
Isn't there another way, Dale?

373
00:34:01,661 --> 00:34:04,234
Watch your step. The timbers are rotten.

374
00:34:04,664 --> 00:34:06,455
Yeah, rotten.

375
00:34:07,374 --> 00:34:10,826
I crashed my motorcycle
on this bridge when I was 14.

376
00:34:12,130 --> 00:34:15,249
The volunteer fire department
had to put it out.

377
00:34:15,549 --> 00:34:18,919
You can still see some of the burn marks.

378
00:34:28,228 --> 00:34:29,391
Perfect hideout.

379
00:34:29,521 --> 00:34:31,016
-Is the old man there?
-Yeah.

380
00:34:31,148 --> 00:34:33,818
-I wonder who else is there.
-He's by himself.

381
00:34:33,942 --> 00:34:35,566
Dale, wait a minute.

382
00:34:36,195 --> 00:34:37,855
It's okay, boys. Come on.

383
00:34:57,090 --> 00:34:58,549
How you doing?

384
00:34:59,926 --> 00:35:01,124
You okay?

385
00:35:01,510 --> 00:35:03,301
-I said, "You okay?"
-I'm doing okay.

386
00:35:03,428 --> 00:35:04,710
That's good.

387
00:35:05,014 --> 00:35:06,472
I'm Chief Dixon.

388
00:35:07,349 --> 00:35:08,927
I'm fixing to do what?

389
00:35:09,226 --> 00:35:10,389
I'm Chief Dixon.

390
00:35:10,520 --> 00:35:14,018
I'm fixing to feed the chickens
before it gets too damn hot.

391
00:35:19,778 --> 00:35:21,736
Have you heard from your nephew lately?

392
00:35:21,948 --> 00:35:23,986
Have you heard from Ray Malcolm?

393
00:35:24,324 --> 00:35:26,945
He's my brother's boy.
I heard of my own kin.

394
00:35:27,077 --> 00:35:30,742
Has he talked to you lately?
When was the last time you talked to him?

395
00:35:30,871 --> 00:35:32,948
-Talked to who?
-Ray Malcolm.

396
00:35:33,208 --> 00:35:35,164
Ray is my brother's boy.

397
00:35:35,293 --> 00:35:39,622
I got to finish feeding these chickens.
It gets hot around here at noontime.

398
00:35:41,173 --> 00:35:44,295
I hope you and them chickens
have a goddamn heatstroke.

399
00:36:05,822 --> 00:36:07,364
Can I help you boys?

400
00:36:24,507 --> 00:36:27,294
"I'm fixing to feed these chickens."

401
00:36:27,843 --> 00:36:31,972
I say, "Have you heard from Ray Malcolm?"
Put that on Daddy's plate, sweetheart.

402
00:36:32,390 --> 00:36:35,805
He says, "Ray Malcolm is my nephew.

403
00:36:36,102 --> 00:36:38,972
"My brother's boy.
I guess I heard of my own kin."

404
00:36:41,232 --> 00:36:43,805
So I said, "Have you spoken to him?"
He said, "Who?"

405
00:36:43,944 --> 00:36:47,146
I said, "Ray Malcolm."
He said, "Ray's my brother's boy."

406
00:36:47,446 --> 00:36:50,400
Imagine the conversation
when Ray shows up.

407
00:36:52,159 --> 00:36:53,321
Rolls?

408
00:36:54,203 --> 00:36:55,578
Is this great or what?

409
00:36:55,704 --> 00:36:57,696
This is great, Cheryl Ann.

410
00:37:02,878 --> 00:37:04,076
There you go.

411
00:37:05,088 --> 00:37:08,837
I hope he does show up.
'Cause I got news for you.

412
00:37:09,217 --> 00:37:11,755
That white trash and
those two niggers are in for--

413
00:37:12,428 --> 00:37:15,346
Cheryl Ann, you nearly broke my--

414
00:37:19,687 --> 00:37:22,141
Bonnie, pass me the pickles.

415
00:37:24,190 --> 00:37:26,561
I never got any beans. May I have some?

416
00:37:42,207 --> 00:37:45,162
Did you think I was going to cut you?

417
00:37:46,878 --> 00:37:49,548
I wouldn't hurt you
for anything in the world.

418
00:37:58,681 --> 00:38:01,469
I'm glad you didn't kill that man
in the car lot.

419
00:38:04,144 --> 00:38:05,853
What do you think we are?

420
00:38:28,793 --> 00:38:30,537
That don't mean nothing, Dale.

421
00:38:30,671 --> 00:38:35,878
What concerns me is that we left ourselves
so goddamn exposed.

422
00:38:36,384 --> 00:38:37,926
So out there.

423
00:38:38,512 --> 00:38:40,634
Anybody could tell
the man wasn't involved.

424
00:38:40,763 --> 00:38:45,591
You can't assume anything about anybody.
That's the guy who will fuck you.

425
00:38:46,103 --> 00:38:49,352
Shit. I've been police chief here for...

426
00:38:50,397 --> 00:38:53,434
...hell, going on six years.

427
00:38:54,694 --> 00:38:56,900
I've never even had to draw my gun.

428
00:39:09,708 --> 00:39:12,330
Come kiss your favourite mommy.

429
00:39:13,545 --> 00:39:15,170
Get in the bed.

430
00:39:16,131 --> 00:39:17,589
Get in there.

431
00:39:18,800 --> 00:39:21,374
-See you in the morning.
-Goodnight, Mommy.

432
00:39:44,491 --> 00:39:47,528
Enjoying yourself?
Getting enough to eat and drink?

433
00:39:47,662 --> 00:39:49,286
Just about.

434
00:39:50,455 --> 00:39:52,531
Isn't that your second bottle?

435
00:39:53,541 --> 00:39:54,824
Yes, it is.

436
00:39:56,129 --> 00:39:58,964
I want to apologise
for that last comment before.

437
00:39:59,464 --> 00:40:01,208
I bet John feels terrible.

438
00:40:02,009 --> 00:40:05,093
Dale didn't mean it.
He just grew up talking that way.

439
00:40:05,344 --> 00:40:07,054
I understand.

440
00:40:08,015 --> 00:40:09,639
I'm sure John does, too.

441
00:40:10,517 --> 00:40:12,924
These people are dangerous, aren't they?

442
00:40:16,647 --> 00:40:17,845
Yes, they are.

443
00:40:18,149 --> 00:40:20,723
I've never seen Dale this excited before.

444
00:40:22,111 --> 00:40:25,895
This case is the biggest thing
that's ever happened to him.

445
00:40:28,951 --> 00:40:31,490
He really likes you and John. I can tell.

446
00:40:32,539 --> 00:40:35,159
I think he looks at you like you're heroes.

447
00:40:36,542 --> 00:40:39,246
Well, we're far from that.

448
00:40:40,003 --> 00:40:42,755
You might want to tell him that.

449
00:40:45,133 --> 00:40:47,625
I have a little girl who needs her daddy.

450
00:40:48,219 --> 00:40:52,431
Dale doesn't know any better.
He watches TV. I read non-fiction.

451
00:41:20,210 --> 00:41:21,703
We better head back.

452
00:41:21,961 --> 00:41:25,247
No, come on guys, the night is young.

453
00:41:26,007 --> 00:41:27,915
-Who wants cookies?
-We all do.

454
00:41:30,136 --> 00:41:32,887
-Very serious meal.
-They're in here.

455
00:41:33,847 --> 00:41:36,254
-I got to go pee.
-Pee off the porch.

456
00:41:36,892 --> 00:41:38,221
Like shit.

457
00:41:45,317 --> 00:41:46,692
You know, Dale...

458
00:41:48,569 --> 00:41:50,443
...this case is our problem.

459
00:41:54,034 --> 00:41:56,822
What I'm saying is,
you can be as involved or...

460
00:41:57,037 --> 00:42:01,165
...uninvolved in the apprehension
of these guys as we want.

461
00:42:02,792 --> 00:42:04,286
Assuming they show up.

462
00:42:04,417 --> 00:42:06,661
If they do, I'll be there.

463
00:42:12,760 --> 00:42:14,550
You got a nice spot here.

464
00:42:19,475 --> 00:42:21,135
Nice house, nice family.

465
00:42:22,519 --> 00:42:23,978
You're a lucky guy.

466
00:42:25,480 --> 00:42:27,556
I guess I am a lucky guy at that.

467
00:42:29,193 --> 00:42:31,185
I hardly ever lose a coin toss.

468
00:42:34,531 --> 00:42:38,114
I go to the horse races,
bet a long shot and it always comes in.

469
00:42:39,035 --> 00:42:41,906
My mama used to say
I was born under a lucky star.

470
00:42:57,886 --> 00:43:01,136
Here's an article about Julia
from Dark Memories.

471
00:43:02,933 --> 00:43:05,638
That ain't Julia.
That's that damn twin sister.

472
00:43:07,396 --> 00:43:08,594
No, it's not.

473
00:43:08,856 --> 00:43:11,013
Ma'am, can you tell him who this is?

474
00:43:11,316 --> 00:43:13,475
That's Julia on Dark Memories.

475
00:43:14,653 --> 00:43:17,226
I told you. You got any maps of Houston?

476
00:43:17,740 --> 00:43:19,779
We don't need no map of Houston.

477
00:43:58,487 --> 00:43:59,897
Be cool.

478
00:44:02,657 --> 00:44:04,068
How are you, Bill?

479
00:44:04,451 --> 00:44:06,443
It's real quiet out there.

480
00:44:08,330 --> 00:44:11,745
I think we got
the two most exciting jobs in town.

481
00:44:13,626 --> 00:44:15,499
Your other burrito is ready.

482
00:44:17,089 --> 00:44:19,543
He's watching me. He knows who I am.

483
00:44:19,966 --> 00:44:22,457
-No, he doesn't.
-He does.

484
00:44:23,677 --> 00:44:25,006
Baby, let's go.

485
00:44:25,220 --> 00:44:27,426
Back up. Just back up.

486
00:44:29,767 --> 00:44:31,759
Ray, stop it. Stop it.

487
00:44:32,896 --> 00:44:33,927
Shit.

488
00:44:45,074 --> 00:44:46,947
I'd never get up on a horse.

489
00:44:48,118 --> 00:44:50,489
-Get your hand off me.
-Let's go.

490
00:44:53,582 --> 00:44:54,781
Let's go, okay?

491
00:44:55,417 --> 00:44:56,876
Don't fuck up, man.

492
00:45:15,727 --> 00:45:17,638
-Will that be all?
-That's it.

493
00:45:17,897 --> 00:45:20,139
Hope you don't mind
that we opened things up.

494
00:45:20,274 --> 00:45:22,018
As long as you pay for it.

495
00:45:24,111 --> 00:45:26,649
You going to drink that beer and drive?

496
00:45:26,947 --> 00:45:29,486
No, we wouldn't do that. This is for later.

497
00:45:31,118 --> 00:45:32,447
Just kidding.

498
00:45:33,078 --> 00:45:34,573
$7.95, please.

499
00:45:53,349 --> 00:45:55,471
-Have a nice night.
-You, too.

500
00:46:03,775 --> 00:46:05,684
She's too young for you, Bill.

501
00:46:07,570 --> 00:46:09,063
I like them young.

502
00:46:26,754 --> 00:46:28,878
Shit! That trooper is behind us.

